Shahruddin bin Md Salleh (Jawi: شهروددين بن مد صالح) is a Malaysian politician. He is the incumbent Deputy Minister of Federal Territories of Malaysia. He is the former Secretary General of the Malaysian United Indigenous Party (BERSATU) and the current Member of Parliament for Sri Gading, Johor.
Shahruddin was formerly a two-term Johor State Legislative Assemblyman for Jorak (2008-2018) and Muhyiddin Yassin's political secretary. He was a member of United Malay National Organisation (UMNO) until he left in 2016 to follow Muhyiddin to set-up the new BERSATU party and become its new secretary-general.


